TITLE: Writing a Row in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to write an array of values to a row in an Excel sheet, starting from a specified cell, using the `excel.write.Row` function. It requires the Excel file handle, sheet name, starting cell reference (e.g., "A1"), and an array of values to be written.
SOURCE: https://github.com/yaoapp/yao/blob/main/excel/README.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/**
 * Writes values to a row starting at the specified cell
 * @param handle - Handle ID from excel.open
 * @param sheet - Sheet name
 * @param startCell - Starting cell reference (e.g. "A1")
 * @param values - Array of values to write
 * @returns null
 */
Process("excel.write.Row", h, "SheetName", "A1", ["Cell1", "Cell2", "Cell3"]);
```

